\f0\b\fs42 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 3. Programmatic Velocity & Humanization Math\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 To prevent your self-generated beats from sounding sterile or robotic, apply a randomized 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Gaussian distribution curve
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 to your note velocities (volume) and timing offsets.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f3\fs22 \AppleTypeServices \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f2\b\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Robotic Beat:
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  Every hi-hat hits at a fixed velocity of 127 and exactly every 0.25 seconds.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f3\fs22 \AppleTypeServices {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f2\b\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Humanized Beat:
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  Python shifts the velocity slightly using a mathematical variance:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0
\AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 $$\\text\{Velocity\} = \\text\{Base Velocity\} + \\mathcal\{N\}(\\mu=0, \\sigma^2=5)$$ \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading40\partightenfactor0

\f5\fs28\fsmilli14118 \AppleTypeServices \cf0 import random\
\
def humanize_note_event(base_velocity=90):\
    
\f4\i # Generates a random float using a normal distribution
\f5\i0 \
    
\f4\i # Keeps velocity fluctuations natural, between roughly -5 and +5 volume points
\f5\i0 \
    variance = random.gauss(0, 2.5)\
    final_velocity = int(base_velocity + variance)\
    \
    
\f4\i # Clip values to legal MIDI boundaries (1-127)
\f5\i0 \
    return max(1, min(127, final_velocity))\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

